owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: If the two ontologies come from the same domain (without any other details).

paradigme de représentation des connaissnces

langage

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: The syntax followed in the creation of an ontology.

type générique

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: Information about who can access the resource or an indication of its security status.

politique des ajouts

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: A class of entity for whom the resource is intended or useful.

contributor

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: An entity primarily responsible for making the resource.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: creator
créateur

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: A related resource that is included either physically or logically in the described resource.

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: A related resource in which the described resource is physically or logically included.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: contrôleur de qualité

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: Indicates that the subject vocabulary generalizes by some superclasses or superproperties the object vocabulary.

has equivalences with

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: Used to assert that two vocabularies are similar in scope and objectives, independently of the fact that they otherwise refer to each other.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: similar to

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: An entity that is a specialization of another shares all aspects of the latter, and additionally presents more specific aspects of the same thing as the latter.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: specializes
spécialise

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: Indicates that the subject vocabulary is used by the object vocabulary.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: used by
utilisé par

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: Comments, typically from users.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: comment
commentaires ou avis d'utilisateurs

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: A work that is a translation of the content of this work.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: traduction de

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: Organization or person who adapts a creative work to different languages, regional differences and technical requirements of a target market, or that translates during some event.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: traducteur

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: This property shall be used to store any analytics for an ontology. E.g., number of visits an ontology received in a portal, number of downloads, etc.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: evaluation based on criteria
évaluation basée sur les critères

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: The method that is followed in evaluating an ontology (e.g., application based approach, assessment by human, data driven approach and golden standard). This property makes a relationship between an ontology and the methodology followed in evaluating the ontology.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: evaluation method
méthode de l'évaluation

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: A group of ontologies that the ontology is usually considered into.

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: An ontology that has been evaluated by an agent.

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: An ontology that is used in a project.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: backward compatible with

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: This indicates that the containing ontology is a later version of the referenced ontology, but is not backward compatible with it.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: incomaptible

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: a été généré par
was generated by

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: Invalidation is the start of the destruction, cessation, or expiry of an existing entity by an activity. The entity is no longer available for use (or further invalidation) after invalidation. Any generation or usage of an entity precedes its invalidation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: a été invalidé par

owl:ObjectProperty.terms:Description: An ontology that is sponsored by and developed under a project.

owl:DatatypeProperty.terms:Description: A short name by which an ontology is formally known.

owl:DatatypeProperty.terms:Description: An alternative name for the resource.

owl:DatatypeProperty.terms:Description: A bibliographic reference for the resource.

owl:DatatypeProperty.terms:Description: The spatial or temporal topic of the resource, the spatial applicability of the resource, or the jurisdiction under which the resource is relevant.

owl:DatatypeProperty.terms:Description: An account of the resource.

This is automatically populated by taking the direct subclasses of owl:Thing If the ontology is also defined as a unique skos:ConceptScheme, then this property should become equivalent of skos:hasTopConcept

owl:DatatypeProperty.terms:Description: Hidden or past name

The hidden labels are useful when a user is interacting with a knowledge organization system via a text-based search function. The user may, for example, enter mis-spelled words when trying to find a relevant concept. If the mis-spelled query can be matched against a hidden label, the user will be able to find the relevant concept, but the hidden label won't otherwise be visible to the user (so further mistakes aren't encouraged).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: hidden label
nom caché ou ancien

owl:DatatypeProperty.terms:Description: Relates an instance of sd:Service to a SPARQL endpoint that implements the SPARQL Protocol service for the service. The object of the sd:endpoint property is an IRI.

point de requêtage SPARQL

représentation
